{This knight jump is my recommendation in Keep it Simple: 1.d4. My main argument favouring the move is that Black needs to be precise to equalize, and it is easy to wrong right away. After 7.Ne5, we need to avoid}
(7.Ne5 Nxd4?? 8.e3! {, which loses on the spot. Better than losing a piece, but still awful, is})
(7.Ne5 Nxe5? {. I'll spare you the details, but rather show what I recommend playing.})

