(9...Bc5 {. I think 9..Be7 is reliable and a bit less effort to study, in comparison. White's typical moves to increase the pressure are Bf4 and Qb3. After 9...Be7, these two moves are the ones to check, leading to different scenarios. Black is fine, but it helps a lot to know the following lines, in particular after})
(9...Be7 10.Qb3 {, which is what I recommended in KIS} 1...d4 {. We reply} 10.Qc7 {, which leads to interesting tactical play. The move @@StartFEN@@r2qk2r/pp1bbppp/2n1pn2/4N3/2Np4/6P1/PP2PPBP/R1BQ1RK1 w kq - 1 10@@EndFEN@@ 10.Bf4 is different, as it prepares to play Qb3 next when ...Qc7 is not possible anymore. We need to play the most precise move to address Qb3, which is 10...Rc8. Let's have a look at the details.})

